# RunPod pod setup — vLLM + ICR gateway (both on pod)

Nothing runs on your Mac except Cursor and `make start/stop`.

## Pod template ports

| Port | Process |
|---|---|
| 8000 | vLLM (Qwen3.6-27B) |
| 8787 | ICR gateway |

## First boot on pod

```bash
# Clone on pod network volume
git clone https://github.com/Johnastc2002/local-ai-agent.git /workspace/local-ai-agent
git clone https://github.com/ryoiki-tokuiten/Iterative-Contextual-Refinements /workspace/Iterative-Contextual-Refinements

cd /workspace/local-ai-agent
cp .env.example .env
# Edit: ICR_REPO=/workspace/Iterative-Contextual-Refinements

# After vLLM is up on :8000:
bash scripts/pod-start-gateway.sh
```

Gateway env (set automatically by script):

```
GATEWAY_ON_POD=1
VLLM_UPSTREAM=http://127.0.0.1:8000
PROXY_PORT=8787
```

## Cursor on Mac

```
make gateway-url
# → https://<POD_ID>-8787.proxy.runpod.net/v1
```

Paste into Cursor Settings → Override OpenAI Base URL.

## Optional: RunPod start command

Add to pod template so gateway starts after vLLM:

```bash
bash /workspace/local-ai-agent/scripts/pod-start-gateway.sh
```

Use `tmux` or a process supervisor if vLLM and gateway start separately.
